&lt;p&gt;At 66degrees, we believe in thriving through challenges and winning together. These values not only guide us in achieving our goals as a company but also for our people. We are dedicated to creating a significant impact for our employees by fostering a culture that sparks innovation and supports professional and personal growth along the way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Overview of Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Cloud Workspace Engineer to lead the initial architecture, design, and implementation of our next-generation digital workspace platform. This role bridges the gap between corporate productivity and developer velocity. You will be responsible for building out a net-new environment from the ground up: streaming business-critical applications to users via Cameyo by Google, while simultaneously provisioning secure, high-performance cloud development environments via Google Cloud Workstations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a role for maintaining a legacy VDI environment. We need an engineer who understands the practical shift toward browser-based, clientless app delivery. You will take full ownership of the initial architecture and map out a clean migration path that is secure from day one.&lt;/p&gt;
